name: T.E. Lawrence
quote: All men dream - but not equally. Those who dream by night in the dusty recesses of their minds wake in the day to find that it was vanity. But the dreamers of the day are dangerous men, for they may act their dreams with open eyes, to make it possible. This I did.

name: Marco Polo
quote: I did not tell half of what I saw, for I knew I would not be believed.

name: Thomas Tew
quote: For those who prove worthy, paradise awaits; for those who prove false, behold your grim fate.
I am a Man of Fortune, and I must seek my Fortune.
name: Henry Avery
Donald Knuth
quote: ...premature optimization is the root of all evil (or at least most of it) in programming.

list.name: Bobby Zimmeruski
list.quote: Do you ever wonder why we're always, like, wearing gloves?

name: Louis Srygleyo
quote: Without requirements or design, programming is the art of adding bugs to an empty text file.

name: Mosher’s Law of Software Engineering
quote: Don’t worry if it doesn’t work right. If everything did, you’d be out of a job.

name: E.W. Dijkstra
quotes: If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.
Program testing can be used to show the presence of bugs, but never to show their absence!

name: Anonymous
quotes: In order to understand recursion, one must first understand recursion.
The best thing about a boolean is even if you are wrong, you are only off by a bit.
